<br>
Toxiss <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufreonsmurf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FreonSmurf</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/22/01 3:57:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=544.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RE:</span><hr size=1> hopefully they will change it and look at the complaints/feedback from those who will actually play a beastlord without a lvl 60 druid sitting beside them <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umistmordra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MistMordra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/11/02 10:57:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=544.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RE:</span><hr size=1> My 17 BL has seen this; unfortunately, it isn't on a pvp server (as it's hard enough just to get one of the damn things to 9, i dont think i could stand  a second) on reflection, i should have started an ogre or a troll (so that i can train without going all the way back to #$%@$% halas because i left luclin too early.... Anyway, their pets are good, and in my opinion, there should be NO spell which just &quot;kills&quot; a pet.. especially for mages/beastlords, as they RELY on their pet, and without it (against anything that can poof their pet) they... just aren't up to par. My pet however, at level 15 could have kicked the crap out of me (30dmgDD, doubles for 1<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  and at 17 i can easily solo with it. (soloed the gnoll side of highpass for 30 minutes until i died, got a yellow of xp and 50pp, nice loot) Unfortunately... well, there's the scary part. the only time i dueled with my BL, it was VS. a melee. They focused on my pet. I thought &quot;well, okay&quot;, ran behind a tree (they didn't even notice) and pressed the pet summon button once it died. I then buffed my pet and sent it back there. Sure enough, i had almost killed her before anything had happened... <br>
Of course being the honorable cat i am, (not wood elf, that's completely different), i backed off before she died and inner fire'd her until she was at full health. <br>
'nuff said, just my input for the dueling capability of a kitty 'lord. (not beastmaster.. that gets me ticked off) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/12/02 10:01:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=544.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RE:</span><hr size=1> Most people I think wouldn't focus on the pet if they were smart.  Id be interested in a few things...<br>
